Slot Description <br>
1:  Increase Max Hitpoints by 46 (L16) to 50 (L20) <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2:  Increase AC by 12 (L16) to 13 (L21)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
3:  Increase Magic Resist by 12 <br>
<br>
Burnout 3<br>
Slot Description <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2:  Increase AC by 13</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
3:  Increase STR by 50 <br>
4:  Increase Attack Speed by 60% <br>
<br>
Xasha, because of the new spell the 50+ firepets cast, Shielding, it and Burnout 3 (our pants, and most mages til they stumble across Burnout 4) are mutually exclusive. Someone posted that earlier. The AC components do not stack if in the same affect slot. By moving the AC component in the Burnout series to another slot, it permits them to stack appropriately.<br>
<br>
On a side thought, this would mean that our Firepets would be able to benefit from a 26 AC boost from Burnout and their own shielding. Enough to do anything? And will changing Burnout's AC component prevent us from using Burnout with any other buffs? I think it'd be rather annoying if some friendly cleric wandered by, buffed our pet some, and we could no longer haste them. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
